  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 230ºC/ 210ºC (fan)/ gas 8</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Trim the green stalk<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> off the <strong>aubergine<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and discard, then chop lengthways into wedges</p><p>Peel and chop the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into wedges</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1582891958576-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1582891958576-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1582891958576-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1582891958576-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1582891958576-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped aubergine</strong> and<strong> onion</strong> to a baking tray with the<strong> dried oregano</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for an initial 12-15 min</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Use 2 trays!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1582891963333-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1582891963333-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1582891963333-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1582891963333-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1582891963333-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Once the aubergine and onion have had 12-15 min, add the<strong> halved cherry tomatoes</strong> to the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> and return to the oven for a further 5 min</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1582891967231-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1582891967231-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1582891967231-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1582891967231-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1582891967231-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst everything is cooking, dissolve the<strong> tomato paste </strong>in 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> balsamic vinegar</strong> and stir it all together – this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Slice the<strong> halloumi </strong>into 6 <span class=\"text-danger\">[12]</span> slices</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1582891974092-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1582891974092-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1582891974092-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1582891974092-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1582891974092-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>tomato stock</strong> to the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></p><p>Top the veg with the<strong> halloumi slices</strong> and return to the oven for a final 10-15 min or until the stock has thickened slightly and the halloumi is golden - this is your <strong>saucy halloumi & roast veg bake</strong></p><p>Tip: To help the sauce thicken, give it a stir half way through</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1582891978064-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1582891978064-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1582891978064-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1582891978064-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1582891978064-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>When the halloumi is almost golden, add the <strong>ciabattas</strong> to a separate baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 5 min or until hot and crusty</p><p>Carefully slice the <strong>warmed ciabattas</strong> in half before serving</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Ciabatta-on-a-baking-tray-1678867062200-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
